commitResults.messageTitle: Enhance date and time validation logic
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, the isValidTime method only checked for the correct format
of time strings but did not validate that the hours and minutes fell
within acceptable ranges. This led to scenarios where invalid times
(like "25:00" or "12:60") were incorrectly considered valid.

Similar issues were encountered with validation of date. Examples
like "2024-03-99, 2023-50-01" were all previously considered
valid.
:q
To address this issue, I have modified the isValidTime method to:
- Split the input string into hours and minutes.
- Validate that hours are between 0 and 23 and minutes are between
  0 and 59.
- Explicitly throw a NullPointerException when the input is null

For the issue of date, instead of using regex for validation,
I used LocalDate parser to check for valid date.

With these changes, the validation process is now more robust,
preventing invalid time strings from being accepted.

commitResults.messageTitle: Modify Address Book to support Events
commitResults.messageBody:
The modifications made are listed below:
* The standard set of methods (add, set, remove, hasEvent) to modify
Events has been added in AddressBook.java.

* A new class UniqueEventList has been created to manage Events within
the Address Book.

Currently, duplicate Events are defined to be events with the same name,
similar to Persons. It can be changed if necessary.

commitResults.messageTitle: Modify Address Book to support Events
commitResults.messageBody:
Method getEventList(), which was left out from the previous commit,
was added to AddressBook.java.

Event class has been created, supporting the creation of events with and
without descriptions so that the description field is optional for the
user to fill in.

Each of its parameters have their respective classes. Below are the
parameters and the data type that they store:
* Name, Location, Description -> String
* startTime, endTime -> LocalTime (using HH:MM format)
* Date -> LocalDate (using yyyy-MM-dd format)

Currently, Date and Time classes' constructors may throw a
DateTimeParseException to catch the user's bad inputs that do not follow
the required format.

Currently UniqueEventList::setEvent is implemented but is not in
use until we decide to add the edit function.

Created another ListView for events to display all events stored
by the user.

Currently it is confirmed to be able to display newly added events.

Support for more advanced functions like search or deleted can be
added in the future.

Address Book now also stores events in its .json file, and will save
any changes made to the list of events similar to the list of persons.

Testcases that are related to Person class has been removed.

Current version only has Checkstyle issues, but passes all testcases.

Either a sizeable chunk of testcases from the following files or
the entire file has been deleted due to the removal of Person class:

Modified:
AddressBookTest.java
JsonSerializableAddressBookTest.java

JsonAddressBookStorageTest.java
ModelManagerTest.java

Deleted:

test.seedu.address.model.person package.

We should consider adding similar testcases back in the future when we
are developing testcases for the application.

GUI can now display Volunteers and their information.

commitResults.messageBody:
Volunteer and Event now have an id field.

GUI displays their id after the name in the following format: (#ID)

Currently ID is not saved in a .json file, and every volunteer and
event will be given a new id in running number each time the
application is booted up. The feature to save IDs in a .json file
can be implemented in the future if deemed necessary.

Currently most of the format is omitted and uses a placeholder
'???'. We should replace them once the command format is specified.

commitResults.messageTitle: Change implementation of opening browser from app
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously java abstract window toolkit api was used to open a
browser from the javafx application. However, there were forum
posts stating that it might not be the best way to implement such
a function due to issues that may arise on mac OS. Thus the
implementation was changed to now use javafx's Application api.

Since the help command now opens the user guide's webpage, there is
no need to maintain the HelpWindow class. The logging of the act
of opening the user guide is now done by MainWindow's logger, and
user guide's url has been shifted to MainApp.java.

The user guide's url has also been updated to the correct url.

commitResults.messageTitle: Change implementation of opening browser from app
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously MainApp's HostServices was passed down to MainWindow
via the constructors of UiManager and MainWindow. However, that
required the modification of the constructors, which was not ideal.

Currently, a new class HostServiceManager is created to handle
storing the HostServices, removing the need to pass the HostServices
through multiple constructors.

AssignCommand now uses the index of events and volunteers as
identifiers instead of their id.
Events and Volunteers no longer have their id displayed on the GUI.

Previously the error message for volunteer index out of bounds
referred to volunteers as persons. It has been changed to refer to
volunteers as volunteers.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix Assign and Unassign error message
commitResults.messageBody:
There was an issue with inconsistent error messages for assign and
unassign raised in #132. This commit resolves the issue raised,
and additionally made the following changes:

* Error message "Index is not a non-zero unsigned integer" is
replaced with "Index has to be a positive integer" when the user
inputs a negative or 0 value as an index.
* Error message displayed after user inputs "unassign" or "assign"
command with missing fields has been changed to the "MESSAGE_USAGE"
strings in their respective classes.

commitResults.messageTitle: Disallow empty description if 'des/' is present
commitResults.messageBody:
The user might have wanted to type in a description but hit the
enter key on accident if the 'des/' prefix is present.

This change prevents users from accidentally creating an event
without a description when they intended for the event to have a
description.

Resolves issue #149.

commitResults.messageTitle: Remove list of matches from find command result
commitResults.messageBody:
If the find command yields too many results, the small window used
to display messages to the user will be overly cluttered with the
names of all the events or volunteers. This commit ensures that
only the details regarding the number of matches are included in
the command result.

Resolves issue #158.

commitResults.messageTitle: Prevent loading overlapping events from json
commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, if the user modifies the json file directly, it is
possible to let VolunSync initialize its database with volunteers
that are assigned to overlapping events. This commit prevents it
from happening.

Resolves issue #156.
